### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:What does sex often make happen in people? Choices:  A: making love B: feel good C: happyness D: wonderful thing E: cloud judgment<n>Output:		D<n><n>### Explanation:<n><n>The first question should be the answer of 140. The correct solution is `140`, although `151` is a better answer. But there is no `148` in the answer choices.<n><n>The second question is trickier. There are both the smallest and the biggest spheres which have diameter of 24 cm (they have the radii 25 cm and 24 cm respectively ). <n><n>The measurement of the rectangular box is 25 cm x 24 cm x 18 cm. 18 cm is the largest spheres` circumference. Therefore, the diameter of this spheres is 9 cm. We multiply the diameter by ` π` to get the volume of the spheres. The correct answer is 2304. There is no 2302 in the choice of answers.<n><n>The third question seems to be the easiest one. We just choose the answer of every choice but the answer 1/28 which is incorrect.<n><n>The last question is even trickier but we can solve it. Choices are in two groups. The first group contains the answer "wonderful" which is actually "wonder". This is not a synonyma for "cloud". So the correct answer in the first group is, "wonderful". "Wonderful" can also be found in the second group while the answer "wonder" cannot. However, "Wonderful" is a bit longer than "wonder", it is 10 characters longer. So "wonderful" has 75% chance to be correct and "wonder" has 25% chance to be the correct one.<n>

Choices:  A: new mexico B: forrest C: dessert D: garden E: creek<n>Output:		B<n><n>Input:There are no right answers<n>Output: B<n>```<n><n>## 자바스크립트를 이용한 한 문제의 풀이<n><n>### Problem Statement :  <n>임의의 행 사이의 겹침은 2임<n>### Solution:  <n>첫 번째 줄에서는 헤더를 검증하는 법을 알아왐야함, 불림굵은 경계만 주석이 되어있음.  <n>```<n>//! @header<n><n>/*<n> * @author : minhoon_04@daum.net, 최혜원(Hyewon Kwak)<n> * @since  20-12-27<n> */<n>```<n>그리고 헤르더를 줄처리했다간에는 그냥<n>```<n>//! //! Comment<n>```<n>임의적으로 헤딩셀을 주석을 사용하였다.  <n>그리고, 난 질문의 겸 모르기를 위해 원문을 살펴보았음.  <n>이를 보면, 아주 특이한 문제이네요.  <n>아 어차피, 원문을 보면 알두아 난 이유가 모르겠네요. 아 어차후 끼어<n><n>한번더.  <n>데이터 그리드이고 이 가맹 유료 이란 아 아냐 아 아룰 아?

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:The people in class were instructed to brainstorm ideas, how would they use their minds for this? Choices:  A: shake hands B: control events C: talk to each other D: think creatively E: dress themselves<n>Output:		A<n><n>Input:13 and 32<n>Output:<n><n>#### Solution::<n><n>First two question the mean is inversely proportional to N the average of n means will be equal to the mean of n mean.<n><n>First two question means the probability of mean equal to 151 and 150. So the probability is 1 / 24 which is almost equal to half.<n><n>Fourth question the mean value is maximum when every element of N is as equal as possible. The volume of the sphere inscribed with the box is minimum when its volume is equal to maximum, which is 3 / 2 X Radius 3 cube.<n><n>Fifth question  The fraction is one-fifteenth or one in every fifteen. The fraction is the remainder of one-seventh of eleven divided by 25.<n><n>Sixth question : the people in 3B want to control the events by thinking. The people in 3A were told to use brainstorm to think creatively and control the event. But people in 3C were shaking hands and people in 3D are talking to each other. And people in 3E are dressing.<n><n>#### Implementation:<n><n>```swift<n>class Solution {<n>    func firstTwoNumbersAddEqual(_ N: Int) -> (Double, Double) {<n>        if N % 2 == 0 {<n>            let half = floor(N / 2)<n>            return (Double(half), Double(half))<n>        }<n>        return (-1.0, 0.0)<n>    }<n>    <n>    func avgIsEqual(N: Int, avg: Double) -> (Double, Bool) {<n>        return (Double(N)/Double(N), avg == Double(N)/Double(Double(1...N)))<n>    }<n>     var ans = N<n>    if N % 2!= 0 {<n>        ans -= 1<n>    }<n>    let (avg, isEqualAverage) = avgIsEqual(ans, avg: avg)<n>    if!isEqualAverage {<n>        return avg<n>    }<n>    var result = (avg, avg)<n>    for _ in 1...3 {<n>        let temp = avg<n>        avg = (avg + 1) /

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:Where does a person need to get when they have more kids? Choices:  A: compliments B: understand themselves C: life partner D: second chances E: larger house<n>Output:		A  ( A as a prefix means more and then kid so it should be more kids. )<n>```<n><n>## Solution<n>```python<n>def main():<n>    question = int(input())<n>    option = range(5)<n>    i=1<n>    while(i<=option.count(option[question])):<n>        if (option[question] == i):<n>            j =0<n>            while(j<=option.count(i)):<n>                print('Ans: {}'.format(j))<n>                j = j+1<n>        i=i+1<n>main()<n>```<n>

The given mean is actually 151 not 148<n>* 2. 25^3 = 2302 not 2304<n>* 3. 1 / 1 / 2 / 2 / 5<n>* 4. it should be breath not breath<n><n>---<n><n>* What is the volume of the greatest sphere that fits in the cube?<n><n>A cube is made up of a lot of faces. A face is a 2-dimensional shape which is bounded by the edge. <n><n>So what do we do?<n><n>- We need to sum up all the faces<n>- We need the volume of each faces to get the total volume of the cube<n><n>So, if you can identify the dimensions of the shape, then you can use the formula of volume to solve the question.<n><n>**The volume of Sphere will be sqrt(3)/6. So the cube would the the cube of the Sphere**<n><n>---<n><n># **Evidence**<n><n><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com

Choices:  A: perfume B: air C: fountain D: swamp E: puddle<n>Output:		puddle.<n><n>## To run:<n>```python<n>import pandas as pd<n>df=pd.DataFrame(data= {<n>    0 : [10,12,10],<n>    1 : [20,20,40]<n>})<n>df_test = (df!= df).astype(float)<n><n>df_test.plot(sort=True,sharey=False,marker="o",color="green",size=5,edgecolor="g")<n><n>df_pred = df_test.apply(lambda x:2*x[0:] + (x[-1] * 0.1))<n>df_pred.plot(sort= True, marker="o",color="red",size=9,xerror=2,label='predicted')<n><n>plt.legend()<n>plt.xlabel('sample')<n>plt.ylabel('estimated Y')<n>plt.show()<n>```

The word you entered is:", answer)<n>else:<n>    print("SORRY, INCORRECT! The word you entered is not here.", inputStr)<n><n>```<n><n>Answer: \section{Solution:}<n><n>\begin{code}<n>import os<n>os.system('clear')<n><n>input_string = input("Enter one or more characters")<n><n>for file in os.listdir("list"):<n>    if (file == input_string.lower()):<n>        print("Correct! ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:The children saw superman fly overhead, what did they exclaim as a result? Choices:  A: ouch B: skip C: enjoyed D: awesome E: watch television<n>Output:		B<n><n>### Solution:<n><n>1. input = list of students and their respective marks.<n>2. 1st, the list is in order so it is already sorted.<n>3. 2nd, sort the list then store it in sorted list'sorted_list'.<n>4. 3rd, using the list sorted_list and the length of the list 'n' as the number of iterations, we start looping from the beginning of the list until the last index of the list.<n>5. For every iteration we will take the 1st student in sorted_list and assign it to key_string variable.<n>6. In the same iteration, we will update key_string by inserting the key of a corresponding dictionary 'values[key_string] = value'<n>7. After iteration we will move our cursor to the next iteration and this process is repeated until all of them are handled.<n>8. When we need to return the result we need only to call.items() to return keys and values pair. the keys are the key_string we assign in the iteration process. <n><n>``` python<n># input<n>list_1 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]<n><n># Sorting function<n>def sorted_list(lst):<n>    sorted_lst = lst<n>    return sorted_lst<n><n># Insert the keys and their values to a dictionary value.<n>def dict_update(key_string, values):<n>    values[key_string]<n><n># Iteration process loop.<n>for key in sorted_list(list_1):<n>    dict_update(key, list_1.count(key))<n><n># return keys and their values.<n>keys, values = dict_update.items()<n><n># values list<n>my_values = []<n><n># Loop to the end of the list to call key_string<n>for key, value in values.items():<n>    my_values.append((key, value))<n><n># return the result.<n>my_output = my_values<n><n>'''out'''<n>'2' '5'<n>```<n><n><n>1. instruction:<n><n>the figure below is divided into 5 parts. The numbers and letter in each part are described. The sum of the numerical (1, 2, …, 5) and the average of the letter is 140. The number 1

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:How can a person end up stopping standing in  puddle? D.<n>Output:d<n></details><n><n>#### Solution:Step by Step by solving questions:<n><n>#### Question-1:<n><n>We can do this in two ways. Either find the mean from all the given 30 data<n><n>Or<n><n>Find the new values without including the data `135` and find the new mean<n><n>Firstly, find the new data without ` 135`<n><n>$$ 108 + 109 + 110 + 111 + 112 + 113 + 114 + 115 + 116 + 117 + 118 + 119 + 120 + 121 + 122 + 123 + 124 + 125 + 126 + 127 + 128 + 129 + 130 \to 14033 $$<n><n><n>![image](/img/b.PNG)<n><n>Now find the mean after applying the above data<n><n>$$ 1403 +33\div 30 \to 60 $$<n><n>This is correct value<n><n><n>So the answer for first ques is (b) 140.22 <n><n>#### Question-2:<n><n>Solution:<n>`(HINT : We have been given the 3 dimensions of a cube but we only want to find a single variable, that is its volume)`<n><n>We can find the volume by finding any two of the dimensions i.e of `length, width & height`<n><n>Since we want to find the volume using 1 variable, let me convert the question<n><n>`= 25  24  25 * 1.25 * 15 / 7`<n><n>`= 100 

[B]<n>![enter image description][2]<n>  input: <n>  mean: 139<n>  mean: 40<n> ![enter image description  here][3] <n>```Python<n>from random import choice, randint, uniform, gauss<n>import numpy as np<n>import sys<n>import math<n>```<n><n>  #### Question1:<n>```Python<n>def q(m):<n>    return -2 * uniform(-1, 1)<n><n>m = choice(10000) #choosing random m between 0 and 39<n>for n in range(1, 40):<n>    if (m - n)**2 <= 0.0001:<n>        return m<n>q8 = randint(0, 9)<n>w = [float(a) for a in q(q8) if (a-1.5)**2 <= 1.2]<n>def a(n):<n>    d = w[n]<n>    return min(d, 50*(max(d, 1)-1)+1)<n><n><n>if __name__ == '__main__':<n>    m = choice(a(5))<n>    print(m + " " + str(m*0.3))<n>```<n>![enter image description  here](Images/image0002.png)<n>Output: the correct mean = [140.00]<n><n> #### Question 2:<n>```Python<n><n>m = [140,160,180,200,220,240]<n>f = 0.003<n>for i in range(m):<n>    if random()<(m/f):<n>        m[i] += 1 <n><n>#get the correct value<n>if __name__=='__main__':<n>	v = 0<n>	for j in m:<n>		if j==m[v] : <n>			v += 1<n>	print(v)<n>```<n>Output: the correct value is 3.<n><n> #### Question 3:<n>```Python<n>from contextlib import redirect_stdout<n>import sys<n><n>from math import pow<n>from random import

Choices:  A: chess set B: strategy C: toy store D: chess game E: small case<n>Output:		d<n><n>#### What are the various elements of a standard instruction? <n>1. Opening line(s): Explains why the instruction was created, and for whom (the teacher or student). In the case of a multiple choice question instruction, the choice(s) are given.<n>1. Antecedent(s)/Reason  The opening line(s) is(are) followed by either a positive outcome or an undesired outcome related to the teaching or learning of the content or skill, this is what drives the instruction and is then referred to as the antecedent(s)/reason statement(s).<n>1."If..." The teacher identifies an event which should happen. The teacher makes a statement about what would happen next if that event occurred. The statement is written in the if condition. The instruction then explains how the teacher and student would respond to the event.<n>1."Then..." The teacher identifies what will happen next. The teacher states how the teacher and student will respond. The steps include the instruction the student needs to follow to address the event and, where applicable, the instruction the teacher should administer to the student.<n>1. Expected Outcomes The instruction ends with statements about how it is expected that both student and teacher will respond to the event after taking these steps.<n>1. Answers Questions: 1. <n><n><n><n>#### How should multiple choice questions be constructed?<n><n>1. Questions: the question must state that it is a multiple choice question<n><n>1. One single option: (give 1 option)<n>a) 1)<n>b) 2)<n>c) 3)<n><n>1. Two single options: (give 2 options)<n>a) 4)<n>b) 5)<n><n>1. Three single options: (gve 3 options)<n>a)6)<n>b) 7)<n>c) 8)<n><n>1. Four single options: (gv 4 options)<n>a)9)<n>b) 10)<n>c) 11)<n>d) 12)<n><n>1. Question format: the question must be of the Multiple Choice format<n><n>1. Option A:<n><p><n>Multiple Choice Question<n>Choose the most appropriate answer from the five (5) choices given:<n></p><n><ul><li>1. (A

A copy error introduced in the computation of these statistics has changed the mean to 50 and the variance to 500. What is the correct answer?<n><n>```<n>$ a) 50, 500<n>$ b) 50, b) 500<n>```<n>It follows that, the actual mean of 30 data is 500, which is quite large. Now, the mean value will become, as required, 50.<n><n>```<n>$ c) 140.5<n>```<n><n><n>Explanation: We have,<n><n>$$\mu_{T} = \frac{30 \times 140}{30} = 50$$<n><n>and<n><n>$$\sigma _{T}^2 = \frac{3(39,5+30,2)}{30} = 39900 \to 500$$<n><n>We have,<n><n>$$s_0^2 = \frac{1500}{26} = 57.69 $$<n><n>Thus, the correct answer lies between $50$ and $500$. Hence, we get the correct answer to be $50$ and not $140.5$.<n><n>Input: What is the diameter of the largest diameter of the largest sphere that will fit into a rectangular box of dimensions $25cm \times 24cm \times 18cm$ $(in $cm$ )$, provided that the bottom of the box is to be used for the base of the sphere?<n><n>```<n> $ e ) 96.4 $\<n>```<n><n>Input:A certain fraction has the same proportion as a certain ratio and as 3/4. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: the mean of 30 values was 140. it was detected on rechecking that one value 145 was wrongly copied as 135 for the computation of the mean. find the correct mean. a ) 151, b ) 140.33, c ) 152, d ) 148, e ) none of the above<n>Output: b<n><n>Input: the measurement of a rectangular box with lid is 25 cmx 24 cmx 18 cm. find the volume of the largest sphere that can be inscribed in the box ( in terms of π cm 3 ). ( hint : the lowest measure of rectangular box represents the diameter of the largest sphere ) a ) 288, b ) 2302, c ) 2304, d ) 8640, e ) 964<n>Output: c<n><n>Input: a certain fraction has the same ratio to 1 / 33, as 3 / 4 does to 7 / 11. what is this certain fraction? a ) 1 / 14, b ) 1 / 18, c ) 1 / 21, d ) 1 / 25, e ) 1 / 28<n>Output: e<n><n>Input:If there is a stale smell in the air coming from the kitchen, what should one check for the source of the smell? Choices:  A: bathroom B: house C: cupboard D: space shuttle E: surface of earth<n>Output:		A<n>Answer<n><n><n><n>### Test 1<n><n>#### Choice A<n><n>Let $R$ be the set of all positive real numbers. I can find the mean of all $30$ real numbers from $R$. I would start by computing the mean from $x = 0$ to $30$ inclusively. This will give the mean of the lowest $30$ numbers. Then I would go from $x = 30$ to $60$ inclusively and compute the mean. Then I would go to $90$ and the mean of all the numbers $0...$ to $90$ inclusively. When looking at the final mean, if the final mean is not within $5$ units of the mean computed from $0...$ to the $30$th number, then I would know for sure that there is a problem with my computation. Thus, for Choice (B), I wouldn't know if there was a problem with my computation or not. It is possible that I could check an incorrect $x$, so I may be wrong.<n><n><n><n>#### Choice B<n><n>This is just the special case where I compute the value from $0$ to $35$ inclusively. It is possible that some value of the original mean lies within $5$ units from the mean computed from $29$ to $64$ inclusively. It could be in the range $5.5$ and $6.5$, so I wouldn't be sure if there was a problem or not. If I add all the numbers in the second set and subtract from the first set, it doesn't guarantee that there is no problem. Even if I get a sum of $0$ I could have an incorrect number. There could be an intermediate correct value that could make the final sum incorrect.<n><n><n><n><n>##### Choice C<n><n>Since I would be checking one value for the entire range of the original mean, I wouldn't be able to be sure if there was an issue. I could, technically, make an error in the calculation.<n><n><n><n>## Solution<n>`Solution: Instruction:<n><n>Input: The  matrix is  xyzabc1234 <n><n>Output: The columns of a matrix can be arranged in any order. So there is an inverse square matrix.  a ) true b ) false<n>Output: c )

Choices:  A: jungle B: bamboo grove C: australian outback D: china E: child's book<n>Output:		B<n><n>'''<n><n>class Solution:<n>    def firstMissingPositive(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:<n>        count = map(lambda x: x in nums, set(nums).difference(set(range(-1, -100, -1))))<n>        count.remove(0)<n>        min_count = min(count)<n>        i = 1<n>        while i < len(nums):<n>            if min_count > 0 and nums[i] < nums[min_count]:<n>                min_count -= 1<n>                i += 1<n>            if min_number == -1:<n>                return i + 1<n>
